            "title": "The Ultimate Guide to Kitchen Vastu for a Happy & Peaceful Home",
            "content_html": "\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">The kitchen is the heart of the home; therefore, it is indispensable to have a positive vibe in the kitchen and avoid all sorts of negative energies. The Vastu Shastra tips that are written in ancient times are impeccable for maintaining positivity in the kitchen. Vastu Shastra is an ancient Indian art that harnesses the energy of natural elements like the heat and light of the sun, the gravitational force of the earth, the direction of the winds, the intensity of rainfall, etc. It uses them to balance with the surroundings of mankind. There are certain rules in Vastu Shastra that are written solely to balance the kitchen interiors from the energies generated by these elements.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-significance-of-kitchen-vastu\">Significance of Kitchen Vastu</h2>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">The kitchen is an integral part of every home. It is considered the second most sacred place in the house, after the pooja room. This is why people spend a lot of money to construct the best kitchen interiors possible, starting from flooring, cupboards, furnishing, counters, etc. But no matter how much people invest in the kitchen, it would still be useless if it is not according to the Vastu Shastra rules.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">The food we cook here on our own and eat differentiates a home from a hotel or any other place. Be it a wife, a husband or a parent and a child, every one of us would have different memories associated with the kitchen. So, as long as food is an essential part of our living, the kitchen will remain an integral part of our home. Hence, Vastu Sastra has given us numerous rules that would help us radiate positive energy in the kitchen at all times.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">For a human to stay healthy and live long, eating nutritious food is a pressing priority. The outside food in restaurants and food courts is entirely unhealthy as we never know what quality of ingredients are used. Make sure that there is always a positive aura in your kitchen.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">Not following the Vastu rules would result in an imbalance of energy in your kitchen, resulting in a high amount of negative energy. This negative energy affects the food made in the kitchen and, thereby, our physical and mental health.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">According to Vastu Shastra, there are 5 key elements in this universe (the Panchatatva) \u2013 namely air, water, earth, space, and fire. Having a perfect balance of all these 5 elements is what makes the kitchen fill with positive energy.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-location-of-the-kitchen\">Location of the Kitchen</h2>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">Where the things inside the kitchen come under secondary, the location of the kitchen is the primary aspect to concentrate on. The kitchen is where we turn raw vegetables, fruits, or nuts into healthy, edible food. For such a process, the key element is fire. Another essential element is water as we use it for cleaning purposes. Balancing these 2 elements, along with the earth, sky, and the air is the key aspect on which the kitchen Vastu is decided.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">According to Vastu Shastra, the South-East direction is related to Agni, the god of fire. Lord Agni represents fire, and since fire is the main element to satisfy the kitchen&#8217;s purpose, the kitchen should be located in the South-East direction.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">While the South-East direction is always the primary choice, finding a house fulfilling this requirement is not always possible. The direction of the kitchen keeps changing depending on the facing of the house. So, in cases where the kitchen is not in the southeast direction, the northwest direction is acceptable.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">Avoid the construction of the kitchen in the north, north-east, or south-west directions as it is strictly against the rules of the Vastu Shastra. Also, the inclination for the flow of water should be from the southwest towards the northeast.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-the-placement-of-the-fire-element\">The Placement of the Fire Element</h2>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">In ancient times wooden logs were used, and over the course of time, the wooden logs were slowly replaced by LPG (Liquified Petroleum Gas) cylinders. Almost all the people in India have shifted to using cylinders like HP or Indane. There is also a further upgrade to using electricity for cooking. But no matter which among the above options it is, the food is still considered to be cooked with the energy of fire. Hence, the placement of all fire elements should be done accordingly.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">The gas stove is the main source of fire, and hence it should compulsorily be placed in the southeast direction. The fire is a huge form of energy and placing the stove in the southeast direction would properly manage and handle that element. Even if it is a northwest kitchen, it should be made sure that the stove is placed in the southeast direction. Another essential point to remember is that the stove should be placed so that the person turning on the stove (i.e., lighting the fire) should always face the east, i.e., we should always be cooking while facing the east direction. The gas cylinders should also be placed in the southeast zone.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">As said above, not just stoves but all appliances, like the electric rice cooker, microwave oven, bread toaster, coffee machine, etc., would all come under things used for cooking and hence they all should also be in the right direction. Since these electrical appliances are also used for cooking, they are also a representation of fire and should be placed in the southeast direction.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-refrigerator-other-appliances\">Refrigerator &amp; Other Appliances</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Electrical appliances like a mixer or wet-grinder should always be preferred to be placed in the northeast direction. But when it comes to heavy machines or utensils, like the fridge or any huge water storage, drums should be placed in the southwest direction.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">No matter where the placement is, always keep in mind that everything should be at least a foot above the floor and a foot away from the corners. Give the slightest preference to the northeast direction when it comes to keeping electrical appliances.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-watch-out-for-the-position-of-the-wash-basin\">Watch Out for the Position of the Wash Basin</h2>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">According to Vastu Shastra experts, water is an opposite element to fire. The fire and water always repel each other, which gives negative energy. Hence, it is important to properly balance the fire and water elements to avoid negative energies in the kitchen. And to balance this, the wash basins or sinks in the kitchen should be placed away from cooking devices. This includes that the stove, gas cylinder, microwave oven, electrical coffee maker, etc., should all not be placed parallel or near the wash basin.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">The north or northeast directions in the kitchen are the best for wash basins and the water pipes connected. In many houses, the washing machine connection is also given in the kitchen. In such cases, the washing machine should also be placed in the northeast direction, but a foot away from the corners and a foot above the ground.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-storage\">Storage</h2>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">Cupboards, shelves, etc., are all storage units where we place all the groceries, grains, rice, and many more ingredients. The placement of storage units is hence important for us to ensure that we are blessed with the groceries all along the year and that we would never run out of shortage.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">All the storage units should be in the kitchen\u2019s southwest direction. If you have a habit of storing cooked food in the kitchen itself, then make sure that you place it in the southwest only.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">Another important point to note is never store grains near the eastern or northern walls.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-entrance-and-ventilation\">Entrance and Ventilation</h2>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">Following the Vastu shastra rules for the kitchen entrance would complete the architecture with everything in the right placements. The entrance could mostly be in either north, east or west directions. There are no specific rules about how the entrance should look, but the only point to remember is, if it is a corner entrance, then make sure to leave at least an inch gap from the wall.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">Windows are also an integral part of the kitchen. Without a window, the kitchen would be suffocated due to the vapors and the smoke coming while cooking. They let in sunlight during the daytime. The windows are also the key opening through which all the negative energy generated in the kitchen gets out. So always make sure to keep the windows open while cooking.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">If there is more than one window, make sure to place them in the same direction. The exhaust fan should also be placed on the same wall as the windows, and a chimney outlet should also be in the east zone.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-flooring-and-wall-colors\">Flooring and Wall Colors</h2>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">Vastu Shastra experts recommended that for the kitchen area the warm and neutral tone colours are the best as it gives out a calm vibe. Hence such pleasant colours should always be preferred.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">The preferable paint colors for kitchen walls are pink, yellow, red, orange, or chocolate brown. There is also a scientific theory that these colors invoke hunger which is an additional plus point. Neither white nor black are preferred, and all extra-dark colors should be avoided.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">The flooring could be of wooden, marble, or ceramic tiles. The cupboard work can be of any material, but make sure that the cupboard colors are also light. If you want to choose dark colors for cupboards, then make sure that they are dark and light.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-can-the-dining-table-be-inside-the-kitchen\">Can the Dining Table be Inside the Kitchen?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">In cases where the kitchen area is huge, some people prefer placing the dining table inside the kitchen itself, instead of having a separate dining room. Vastu Shastra does not oppose the dining table in the kitchen, but care should be taken in its placement. According to the Vastu Shastra, the dining table should be placed in the northwest direction and never be in the center of the kitchen. If the northwest is occupied, then try either the north or the west direction.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify\">Also, make sure that there is no bathroom entrance facing the dining table.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-some-important-points-to-remember\">Some Important Points to Remember</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>The kitchen should never be located under or above the bedroom, pooja room, or bathroom.</li><li>The Vastu Shastra also states that it is unhealthy for the kitchen and a bathroom to share a common wall.</li><li>The stove or the gas cylinder should never be directly in front of the kitchen\u2019s entrance.</li><li>Heavy things should never be placed in the east or north directions of the kitchen.</li><li>The kitchen dustbin should be under the kitchen sink, and make sure to place all wastes in the dustbin. The dustbin should also be cleared regularly.</li><li>The kitchen should be neat and clean to ensure positive energy at all times.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-you-might-also-like\">You Might Also Like</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-yoast-seo-related-links\"><li><a href=\"https://www.squareyards.com/blog/kitchen-vastu-defects\">Kitchen Vastu Defects and Some Common Remedies</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.squareyards.com/blog/top-5-tips-for-a-sustainable-home\">Top 5 Tips for a Sustainable Home</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.squareyards.com/blog/vastu-for-flats\">Vastu for Flats &amp; Apartments: 15 Major signs to watch out for</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.squareyards.com/blog/how-to-fight-with-coronavirus\">How to Fight with Coronavirus?</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.squareyards.com/blog/west-facing-house-vastu-plan-tips\">West Facing House Vastu Plan &amp; Tips</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-frequently-asked-questions-faq-s\">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ&#8217;s)</h2>\n\n\n        <section class=\"sc_fs_faq sc_card\">\n            <div>\n\t\t\t\t<h2>In which direction should a window be placed in the kitchen?</h2>                <div>\n\t\t\t\t\t                    <p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tThe windows should be placed on the east or west side of the kitchen, preferably east.                    </p>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </section>\n\t        <section class=\"sc_fs_faq sc_card\">\n            <div>\n\t\t\t\t<h2>Can I hang a clock in the kitchen?</h2>                <div>\n\t\t\t\t\t                    <p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tIf you want to hang a clock, prefer the south or the south-west wall.                    </p>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </section>\n\t        <section class=\"sc_fs_faq sc_card\">\n            <div>\n\t\t\t\t<h2>Where can Water storing commodities be located?</h2>                <div>\n\t\t\t\t\t                    <p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tWater storing commodities like earthen pots, water filters, RO purifiers, etc., should also be pla