            "content_html": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You must already know about a <strong>Laughing Buddha </strong>or a <strong>Buddha statue </strong>that is commonly used in so many homes. There are several shades and layers to the question if you are seeking the <strong>Buddha meaning </strong>or planning to install a <strong>Buddha statue for home</strong>. As per Vastu Shastra guidelines, a <strong>smiling Buddha </strong>or Laughing <strong>Buddha idol</strong> is a sign of prosperity and should be there in each household. It is a symbol of much happiness and may help in infusing more positive vibes into the household. Putting a Laughing <strong>Buddha face</strong>, statue or <strong>Laughing Buddha images </strong>in the right place will go a long way towards infusing suitable cosmic energy while relieving all stress and tension in the bargain.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Before choosing Laughing or <strong>Peace Buddha images</strong> and choosing <strong>stone Buddha statue</strong>s among those in other materials, you should know the real story behind the legend. <em>Pu-Tai</em> or <em>Hotei</em> is called the Laughing Buddha. The image of Hotei has been made on the basis of the Chinese Zen monk who lived more than 1000 years earlier. Many saw him as a future Buddha owing to his generosity and benevolence. It was on account of his huge protruding belly and iconic smile/laugh that people started calling him as the Laughing Buddha. Getting a <strong>Laughing Buddha statue </strong>is highly auspicious for any home. You should however, keep your <strong>Lord Buddha statue</strong> in a suitable location. It is not considered lucky or auspicious to keep your <strong>marble Buddha statue </strong>or a Buddha statue in any other material outside your house. This is because Vastu Shastra principles clearly state that the living room is the best place for a <strong>Buddha statue for home d\u00e9cor</strong> purposes.</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Keeping the Buddha Statue before the main entrance</strong></h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You may opt to keep your <strong>Laughing Buddha gift </strong>received from a loved one or bought yourself, before the main entrance of your home. Make sure that this stays at the primary entrance. You should ensure that the height is at eye level or slightly higher. You should never look at this from above. For drawing more prosperity and wealth or using what is the <strong>money Laughing Buddha</strong> effect, make sure you have the statue close towards the primary home entrance.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Apart from Laughing varieties, there are several options available including peaceful motifs, <strong>white Buddha statue</strong>s and other <strong>small Buddha statue</strong>s showcasing the idol in various moods. These include <strong>sleeping Buddha statue</strong>s and even <strong>meditation Buddha images</strong> and postures. Choose carefully.</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Laughing &amp; Meditating Buddha Idol</strong></h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For a peaceful and happy life, get a Laughing Buddha in a meditative state. This will help in relieving stress at home and keep this in the bedroom, prayer or worship room and the study.</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Laughing Buddha with Wo Lu</strong></h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">A statue of Laughing Buddha with Wo Lu is essential for safeguarding health. This statue should be present in the eastern direction of the living room or bedroom. This will enhance health of every individual in the household.</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Dragon Tortoise Buddha Statue</strong></h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This statue of the Laughing Buddha positioned upon a dragon tortoise indicates ample strength and power in turn. Bringing this home will help you boost your career and income levels. You can keep this behind your desk at work and it will positively impact your business or professional life.</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Eastern Direction for Laughing Buddha Statues</strong></h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Vastu Shastra mandates keeping Laughing Buddha statues in the eastern direction of the home. This will help in infusing more harmony and joy into any home while nipping arguments and tension in the bud. You can also put a statue on the office or study desk for improving concentration and eliminating mental distractions while combating chances of arguments and quarrels with partners and colleagues at work.</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Laughing Buddha with Gold Coins</strong></h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">One of the best Vastu tips is getting a statue of Laughing Buddha with a sack of gold coins on the shoulder. This indicates good luck and happiness for all family members. You may also control any negative energy by putting this in the living room. A golden colored statue will naturally bring more positive vibes into any space.</p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Where Shouldn\u2019t You Keep the Laughing Buddha? </strong></h3>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Laughing Buddha is a worshipped deity and the statue should never be there in the toilet, bathroom and kitchen. Based upon principles of Vastu Shastra, these places are not auspicious for the statue and should be strictly avoided as a result. You should never keep the statue on the floor of the house as well.</p>\n<p><strong>ALSO READ :</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"card-title\"><a title=\"East Facing House Vastu Plan: Know all Details for a Peaceful Life\" href=\"https://www.squareyards.com/blog/east-facing-house-vastu-plan\">East Facing House Vastu Plan:&nbsp;</a></li>\n<li class=\"card-title\"><a title=\"Prayer Room Vastu Shastra Tips For A Peaceful Home\" href=\"https://www.squareyards.com/blog/prayer-room-vastu-shastra-tips-