entrance of the house faces towards the east direction. In other words, if you are facing the east side when inside the house while walking out of the house, then it is an east-facing house.\u00a0</p>\r\n<p><strong>Are East-Facing Houses Lucky?\u00a0</strong></p>\r\n<p>It is widely believed that east-facing houses are all auspicious. However, this is not the case. While east-facing houses are favourable, not all have equally sound attributes in compliance with Vastu Shastra. While direction and orientation play a crucial role, essentially, homes that are broad as well as at a lower level are considered the luckiest. Typically, such homes are more suitable in buildings, multi-storey apartments, and individual spaces.\u00a0</p>\r\n<p><strong>Vastu Tips For East-Facing Homes\u00a0</strong></p>\r\n<p>One of the most essential factors to consider is your\u00a0<strong>East-facing home Vastu plan.\u00a0</strong>While such homes are generally auspicious in Vastu terms, there are a few tips and tricks that can be tweaked and incorporated to make them more favorable. While for individual bungalows and villas, east-facing is not as desired, they work great for multi-storey apartments and building flats. Some Vastu tips and guidelines to follow for east-facing houses that will help you are stated below.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Use a magnetic compass to measure the accurate east direction of the plot.\u00a0</li>\r\n<li>An\u00a0<strong>east-facing house Vastu plan with pooja room should</strong> have the said room in the northeast zone of the space. This is considered auspicious and brings in serenity.\u00a0</li>\r\n<li>If there is a staircase in your house, the best direction for it is on the south or west.\u00a0</li>\r\n<li><strong>Living rooms in an east-facing house should</strong> be placed in the northeast direction for bringing out the ultimate result as per Vastu norms.\u00a0</li>\r\n<li>A master bedroom should have a southwest direction for optimum Vastu compliance.\u00a0</li