 clutter or dirt-related items such as trash cans should be placed in the north or the northeast corner of the house.\u00a0</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>By considering the above-mentioned points, you will avoid negativity, bad ventilation, lack of peace, and the overall offerings of Vastu Shastra.\u00a0</p>\r\n<p><strong>The Importance of Vastu Shastra for Every Room\u00a0</strong></p>\r\n<p>While there is a general belief and strategy related to Vastu Shastra, every room has its importance and can differ in terms of design and placement. While some can be tweaked in marginal ways, a complete opposite of following Vastu rules can lead to adverse circumstances, putting the peace of the entire house in jeopardy. Let us take a look at the following mentioned important rooms of a home and how you can imbibe Vastu into them.\u00a0</p>\r\n<p><strong>Master Bedrooms\u00a0</strong></p>\r\n<p>\u00d8\u00a0<strong>Master bedrooms Vastu for east-facing houses</strong>\u00a0should ideally be planned in the southwest direction.</p>\r\n<p>\u00d8 The bed should be placed on the south or west side of the walls, ensuring that the head lies in the west or south direction and the legs are in the east or north direction.\u00a0</p>\r\n<p>\u00d8 Changing rooms within the master bedroom should be on the north or west side of the bedroom.\u00a0</p>\r\n<p>\u00d8 The master bathroom should not be facing the bed directly and the entrance door to the bathroom should always remain closed.\u00a0</p>\r\n<p>\u00d8 No mirror should be placed right in front of the bed or on any surface that might allow for your reflection to show when you are on it.\u00a0</p>\r\n<p><strong>Living Rooms\u00a0</strong></p>\r\n<p>\u00d8 Living room for Vastu east-facing houses should be in the north-east direction. This is considered auspicious.\u00a0</p>\r\n<p>\u00d8 The walls of the living room which are on the north and east sides should be marginally thinner as well as shorter than the others. This is expected to help in bri