not as desired, they work great for multi-storey apartments and building flats. Some Vastu tips and guidelines to follow for east-facing houses that will help you are stated below.\r\n\r\nUse a magnetic compass to measure the accurate east direction of the plot.\u00a0\r\nAn\u00a0east-facing house Vastu plan with pooja room should have the said room in the northeast zone of the space. This is considered auspicious and brings in serenity.\u00a0\r\nIf there is a staircase in your house, the best direction for it is on the south or west.\u00a0\r\nLiving rooms in an east-facing house should be placed in the northeast direction for bringing out the ultimate result as per Vastu norms.\u00a0\r\nA master bedroom should have a southwest direction for optimum Vastu compliance.\u00a0\r\nIdeally, guest bedrooms should be placed in the north-west direction\r\nIn case a student lives in this house, you should place a crystal globe in the northeast direction.\u00a0\r\nThe south and west direction walls should be thicker and longer than the north and east direction walls.\u00a0\r\nPlacement of the kitchens is an important aspect. The kitchen should strategically be placed in the northwest or southeast direction of the house.\u00a0\r\nThe person who is cooking should be facing the east direction in a south-east facing kitchen and west in a north-west facing kitchen.\u00a0\r\nBalconies, open atriums, vestibules, and all other open spaces should be placed in the east of the house. This ensures good ventilation along with positive energy and strong vibes.\u00a0\r\nSalt is considered a universal healer hence it is advised that rock salt should be placed in all corners of the house.\u00a0\r\nPyramids are a popular Vastu weapon and can easily be purchased in the market and placed in areas such as kitchens, bedrooms, living rooms, and practically anywhere as per the guidance of your Vastu consultant. This avoids discrepancies if any, in the home.\u00a0\r\n\r\nVastu for East-Facing Main Entrance Doors\r\nThe main entrance door is a crucial factor and should be placed exactly in the middle. Ensure that it is not placed in either the southeast or northeast directions as that will hamper the harmony of the overall vibe. Tips of\u00a0Vastu for east-facing main doors\u00a0are mentioned here.\r\n\r\nIn case the entrance is in the northeast corner, ensure that the main door is not in contact with the northeast corner. Leave a minimum 6-inch gap between the door and the wall.\u00a0\r\nIn the case of a south-east facing entrance, you can place three Vastu pyramids, one on the top of the main door in the center and two on either side.\u00a0\r\nYou can install a Siddha Shukra Tantra to get rid of all the negative energy in the room.\u00a0\r\nUse a Siddha Vastu Kalash to boost the positive energy which can be generated from the corner of the house.\r\n\r\nPlan for an East-Facing Vastu House\u00a0\r\nFor those constructing an east-facing home, it is pertinent to adhere to Vastu Shastra to facilitate positive energy. While many interior designers and architects follow basic Vastu, for those who want in-depth compliance with the science, Vastu Shastra experts can also be consulted. The following table demonstrates in what direction your east-facing home should be designed as per Vastu stated norms.\u00a0\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nS. No. \r\n\r\n\r\nType of Room\r\n\r\n\r\nPreferred direction as per Vastu Shastra\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n1\r\n\r\n\r\nGuest room, kitchen, living room\r\n\r\n\r\nNorth-West\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n2\r\n\r\n\r\nDrawing room, living room, office\r\n\r\n\r\nNorth\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n3\r\n\r\n\r\nPooja Room\r\n\r\n\r\nNorth-East\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n4\r\n\r\n\r\nStudy room, dining room, children&#8217;s room\r\n\r\n\r\nWest\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n5\r\n\r\n\r\nVerandah, atrium, entrance lobby, balconies and other open spaces\r\n\r\n\r\nEast\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n6\r\n\r\n\r\nStaircases, overhead tanks\r\n\r\n\r\nSouth\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n7\r\n\r\n\r\nKitchen, bathrooms, staircases\r\n\r\n\r\nSouth-East\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n8\r\n\r\n\r\nStorerooms, garages, master bedrooms\r\n\r\n\r\nSouth-West\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n9\r\n\r\n\r\nMain doors\r\n\r\n\r\nRight in the Centre\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\u00a0Vastu Don&#8217;ts for East-Facing Homes\u00a0\r\nWhen designing a Vastu compliant east-facing house, make note of the following mentioned don&#8217;ts that should be avoided. To make your life easier, have a look at the list below of\u00a0things to avoid in east-facing homes.\u00a0\r\n\r\nNo septic tanks should be placed in the northeast corner of the home.\u00a0\r\nPlacing a kitchen in the northeast direction is a huge no.\u00a0\r\nStaircases if any, should not be constructed in the northeast direction.\u00a0\r\nGarages if any, should not be placed in the northeast direction.\u00a0\r\nNo large trees should be planted in the north as well as the east direction.\u00a0\r\nIn bedrooms, it is not advisable to place a mirror right in front of the bed so that your reflection is not visible when you are in bed.\u00a0\r\nThe whole premises should not have any slope from the north to south direction.\u00a0\r\nNo heavy blocking or packing should be in the northeast direction.\u00a0\r\nMain entrances should not have any object blocking them such as poles, trees, artifacts, large statues, etc.\u00a0\r\nNo clutter or dirt-related items such as trash cans should be placed in the north or the northeast corner of the house.\u00a0\r\n\r\nBy considering the above-mentioned points, you will avoid negativity, bad ventilation, lack of peace, and the overall offerings of Vastu Shastra.\u00a0\r\nThe Importance of Vastu Shastra for Every Room\u00a0\r\nWhile there is a general belief and strategy related to Vastu Shastra, every room has its importance and can differ in terms of design and placement. While some can be tweaked in marginal ways, a complete opposite of following Vastu rules can lead to adverse circumstances, putting the peace of the entire house in jeopardy. Let us take a look at the following mentioned important rooms of a home and how you can imbibe Vastu into them.\u00a0\r\nMaster Bedrooms\u00a0\r\n\u00d8\u00a0Master bedrooms Vastu for east-facing houses\u00a0should ideally be planned in the southwest direction.\r\n\u00d8 The bed should be placed on the south or west side of the walls, ensuring that the head lies in the west or south direction and the legs are in the east or north direction.\u00a0\r\n\u00d8 Changing rooms within the master bedroom should be on the north or west side of the bedroom.\u00a0\r\n\u00d8 The master bathroom should not be facing the bed directly and the entrance door to the bathroom should always remain closed.\u00a0\r\n\u00d8 No mirror should be placed right in front of the bed or on any surface that might allow for your reflection to show when you are on it.\u00a0\r\nLiving Rooms\u00a0\r\n\u00d8 Living room for Vastu east-facing houses should be in the north-east direction. This is considered auspicious.\u00a0\r\n\u00d8 The walls of the living room which are on the north and east sides should be marginally thinner as well as shorter than the others. This is expected to help in bringing success in both, professional as well as personal lives.\u00a0\r\nPooja Rooms\u00a0\r\n\u00d8 Pooja room Vastu in the east-facing house is typically supposed to be in the northeast direction. As this is the most important room for religious people, no alterations should be made for its placement.\u00a0\r\nKitchens\r\n\u00d8 Kitchens are an important part of the house and need to be placed in the southeast or northwest direction of the house.\u00a0\r\nWhile the above-mentioned rooms are the main ones, other rooms such as guest rooms, balconies, study rooms, children&#8217;s rooms, etc. also each have their own sets of rules as per Vastu Shastra and have been mentioned in the table in the segment above. Every corner of every room in an east-facing house should be adhered to and followed in accordance with Vastu Shashtra.\r\nPaints colours for east-facing rooms\r\nIn east-facing rooms, there is ample sunlight in the morning and artificial lights will be required in the afternoon and thereafter. Before selecting the colour for your east-facing rooms or house, try to visualize them with both artificial and natural light. Usually, hues of blue and green are the recommended shades for east-facing rooms. A shade of green is all about adding a fresh vibe and blue is sure to make your room look cool.\r\nEach house is as unique as the individual that buys it. While not everyone is suitable for each other, neither are houses. In an\u00a0East-facing house, sunlight\u00a0is a prominent factor and relates directly to power, authority, and dominance of sort. The east direction is favourable and demonstrates the representation of protection, agility, focus, and creativity. When asking the question\u00a0of who are suitable for east-facing houses, the favourable winners of the spectrum are government jobholders, businessmen, and those in the field of creativity. Regardless, east-facing houses are popular for those looking for Vastu compliant homes due to their ventilation, sunlight, and overall airy atmosphere. If designed properly, they can create a life full of love, joy, and harmony and improve the general standard of living.\u00a0\r\nEast facing house Vastu plan with Pooja room \r\nYou will find several available options for east facing house Vastu plan with pooja room online. These are different from north east facing house Vastu plans or any north east facing house. Here are some important pointers that you should keep in mind above all else:\r\n\r\nWhile considering an East facing house Vastu plan, remember that east-facing properties are usually suitable for multistoried apartments and buildings. Independent houses and bungalows will not have this east facing house plan as per Vastu. They will have varying plans for east facing house Vastu plan with pooja room.\r\nCheck out nort