            "content_html": "\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://www.squareyards.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/image-72.png\" alt=\"Mirror Vastu\" class=\"wp-image-20327\" width=\"324\" height=\"194\"/></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-mirror-in-bedroom-vastu\">Mirror in Bedroom Vastu</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Are you planning to set up a beautiful&nbsp;<strong>mirror in bedroom</strong>&nbsp;to adorn yourself and the beauty of your room? Well based on the positioning of mirrors in your bedroom, here are some of the conditions as per the Vastu Shastra to turn your home Vastu Compliant.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Basically, as per the Vastu Shastra, experts recommend not to place a mirror in your bedrooms.</li><li>However, if you do have one,&nbsp;<strong>mirror in bedroom Vastu&nbsp;</strong>recommends toplace it either on the west or south wall.</li><li>Note that, mirrors shouldn\u2019t be hung opposite to your bed as it could have adverse effects on your living conditions.</li><li>Likewise, mirrors facing north and east directions are believed to drive away the positive energy entering your rooms by reflecting it.</li><li>Therefore, while placing a mirror on your bedroom, make sure it reflects beautiful views outside to bring in the positive flow of energy into your rooms.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Vastu Shastra poses that mirrors might trigger sleeplessness when positioned in the bedrooms. Furthermore, when placed opposite the bed, a third party that is the negative energy could intrude on you while bonding with your partner.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-what-is-vastu\">What is Vastu?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Vastu is an ancient study that focuses on the flow of energy. This scientific study focuses on both positive and negative vibes that surround us. People tend to be drawn towards Vastu Compliant homes to lead happy and healthy lives.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Therefore, in this article, we present the various aspects of the Vastu Shastra to make your homes Vastu Compliant. You can even lookup Vastu for different rooms in your language to understand the concept better. For example, people search for&nbsp;<strong>bedroom Vastu in Telegu&nbsp;</strong>and likewise you could do the same.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"h-some-do-s-and-don-ts-of-vastu\">Some Do\u2019s and Don\u2019ts \u2018of Vastu</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Focus on the east.</li><li>Install a name frame at a height.</li><li>Sleep facing the south.</li><li>Don\u2019t plant cactus or other prickly plants indoors.</li><li>Don\u2019t store waste and unused items that are old and worn out.&nbsp;</li></ul>\n\n\n<h2>Crosscheck the following aspects of mirrors while buying from a Mirror Shop</h2>\n<p>Buying mirrors from the&nbsp;<strong>mirror</strong>&nbsp;<strong>shop</strong>&nbsp;is as important as placing one in your home. Let us take a look at the aspects of buying a mirror:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The&nbsp;<strong>house front mirror design</strong>&nbsp;should possess the finest quality glass having a thick and silver lining.</li>\n<li>Check for inconsistencies and distorted reflectiveness.</li>\n<li>Look into the various shapes and sizes when opting to buy wall mirrors.</li>\n<li>Full length and&nbsp;<strong>dressing</strong>&nbsp;<strong>mirror</strong>s need to be placed either on a freestanding or could also be hung. Make sure to buy long and narrow&nbsp;<strong>dressing</strong>&nbsp;<strong>mirrors for bedroom</strong>&nbsp;as they are proposed to reflect your full-length reflection.</li>\n<li>There is one more category of freestanding mirrors or the leaning ones for&nbsp;<strong>dressing mirror cover</strong>. These are also full-length mirrors that do not require to be mounted on the walls.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>What is Mirror Vastu?</h2>\n<p>Mirrors are a great option to go for when it comes to select the best home d\u00e9cor. They contribute to making your home attractive by giving a brighter and spacious appeal. However, as per the Vastu Shastra, there are several aspects to keep in mind while designing your home with the help of mirrors. Some of the key pointers are discussed below based on&nbsp;<strong>Mirror Vastu</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Mirrors should be placed on the West and South Walls.</li>\n<li>Mirrors should be placed adjacent to the entrance and not opposed to it.</li>\n<li>Dining and Living Rooms are the ideal choices to place mirrors.</li>\n<li>Mirrors should not oppose the north and east directions of your home.</li>\n<li>Bedroom mirrors should not face the bed.</li>\n<li>Circular Mirrors should be hung in living rooms and not rectangular.</li>\n<li>Whereas, rectangular or square mirrors should be used when using the&nbsp;<strong>mirror facing south</strong>&nbsp;or west wall.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"300\" height=\"168\" src=\"https://www.squareyards.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/image-73.png\" alt=\"vastu for mirror\" class=\"wp-image-20328\"/></figure></div>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Negative Effects of Placing a Mirror in the Wrong Direction</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, there are also negative effects of placing a mirror in the wrong place or directions and you should rectify them accordingly. Some of those instances are:&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Fixing a mirror in the south-east direction (also known as the fire direction) can increase the chances of disagreements and quarrels.</li><li>No two mirrors should be placed side by side or it can cause restlessness among family members.&nbsp;</li><li>According to <a href=\"https://www.squareyards.com/blog/vastu-for-flats\">Vastu</a> Shastra, mirrors should not face in the east or north direction at an entrance. In doing so, you may increase your chances for attracting negative energy and worsen the positive energy.</li><li>It is best to avoid placing a mirror in the bedroom because it can cause nightmares and sleep disturbances. In case of a Vastu mirror position in your bedroom, please make sure it does not face the bed.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Important tips on Vastu mirror position:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Avoid oval-shaped mirrors instead use rectangular or square mirrors.</li><li>Mirrors in a bathroom should not be kept dark but adequately lighted.&nbsp;</li><li>In the case of chronic sleeplessness or nightmares, placing a mirror between the bed and mattress (facing upward) can reduce the symptoms.</li><li>Mirrors positioned at the entrance should not reflect sunlight or it can bring negative energies.&nbsp;</li><li>Always get rid of a broken or tainted mirror to let the positive aura grow in your home</li><li>Looking at oneself during sunrise in a big mirror placed on the dressing table will bring good luck.</li><li>Avoid hanging a mirror on the south walls and cover all glass window panes/glass doors at night to prevent yourself from adversities.&nbsp;</li><li>Lastly, do not place two mirrors opposite to each other because it may create anger, impatience and misunderstanding among family members.&nbsp;</li></ul>\n\n\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Factors affecting Mirror in Bedroom Vastu&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The bedroom is the ultimate space to relax and rejuvenate after a day\u2019s work. However, while planning your bedroom, you should look for the following aspects for&nbsp;<strong>mirror direction in bedroom</strong>&nbsp;to make it Vastu Compliant:</p>\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<li>Mirrors should not be placed opposite your beds. That is,&nbsp;<strong>mirror position in bedroom as per Vastu</strong>&nbsp;should not face the bed. The&nbsp;<strong>mirror in front of bed&nbsp;</strong>is highly not recommended by Vastu Shastra Experts.</li>\n<li>Your sleeping position should not be reflected in the mirror. This could trigger insomnia and restlessness.</li>\n<li>Mirrors when placed across the bed could drive a negative force that could intrude on husband-wife relations.</li>\n<li>It is best to avoid mirrors in the bedroom. However, if you still wonder&nbsp;<strong>where to put a mirror in bedroom</strong>, then make sure to place it such that you could cover it up before you go to sleep.</li>\n<li>Also, do not place it in the south-east&nbsp;<strong>mirror</strong>&nbsp;<strong>direction</strong>.&nbsp;<strong>Vastu Mirror Position</strong>&nbsp;experts do not recommend this angle as it is considered to be unlucky.</li>\n<li><strong>Mirror direction <a href=\"https://www.squareyards.com/blog/vastu-for-toilets-bathrooms\">Vastu</a>&nbsp;</strong>suggests to avoid placing the&nbsp;<strong>mirror</strong>&nbsp;<strong>opposite</strong>&nbsp;to each other.</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Various Shapes and their Vastu on Wall Dressing Mirror</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Shapes and sizes are as important as the positioning of the Mirrors. Let us take a look at what shapes go well with&nbsp;<strong>wall dressing mirror</strong>&nbsp;at the various corners of your home:</p>\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<li>When placing a&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://www.squareyards.com/blog/6-ways-mirrors-make-a-home-look-bigger\">mirror</a> as per Vastu</strong>&nbsp;on the north-facing walls, you must avoid square-shaped ones. Instead, you could go for circular, rectangular, diagonals, or any of that sort.</li>\n<li><strong>Mirror placement on the wall </strong>to face the east should be done with either rectangular or square mirrors. Circular mirrors should completely be avoided if you wish to make&nbsp;<strong>mirror placement as per Vastu</strong>.</li>\n<li>North-east facing walls are best to place the round or rectangular shaped mirrors.</li>\n<li>West walls too are nearly perfect for round and square-shaped mirrors.</li>\n<li>South-east and south-west walls must be completely devoid of any mirrors.</li>\n<li>You can still set&nbsp;<strong>mirror position as per Vastu</strong>&nbsp;on the walls facing south.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Factors to keep in mind for Mirror Placement in Living Room</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Living rooms are the centre of your homes. Placing a mirror in the living room is an ideal choice. However, keep the following factors in mind before making&nbsp;<strong>mirror placement in the living room</strong>:</p>\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<li>Mirrors reflect positive and negative energy in the living room.</li>\n<li>Based on the vibe of the guests, your home could be drawn to positivity as well as negativity.</li>\n<li>If your living rooms open up to a beautiful view with gardens and greenery around, make sure to place the various&nbsp;<strong>home front mirror design</strong>&nbsp;at an angle to reflect the outside views.</li>\n<li>Place the&nbsp;<strong>mirror</strong>&nbsp;<strong>on</strong>&nbsp;<strong>the west wall Vastu&nbsp;</strong>at a height, that is, above the ground level.</li>\n<li>Rectangular, Square and Circular Shaped&nbsp;<strong>mirror in</strong>&nbsp;<strong>Living room Vastu</strong>&nbsp;is recommended. Avoid irregular shaped mirrors for living rooms.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Role of Dressing Table with Mirror on it</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Many ask&nbsp;<strong>where to place the dressing table in bedroom as per Vastu</strong>. Here are some of the suggestions to set a&nbsp;<strong>dressing table Vastu&nbsp;</strong>or any&nbsp;<strong>almirah with mirror Vastu&nbsp;</strong>in your bedroom.</p>\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<li>Mirrors in&nbsp;<strong>wardrobe facing Vastu&nbsp;</strong>should be positioned in such an angle that it does not appear opposing the bed.</li>\n<li>It should either be adjacent to the main door and avoid south-east positioning.</li>\n<li>The&nbsp;<strong>best position for dressing table&nbsp;</strong>would solely depend on the length and breadth of your room.</li>\n<li>Therefore, before you buy any home, make sure it is Vastu compliant.</li>\n<li>However, if your dressing table faces the bed, you can still modify it by adding a&nbsp;<strong>dressing mirror cover&nbsp;</strong>to it.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Wardrobe Position As per Vastu</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Here are some tips for&nbsp;<strong>Wardrobe direction as per Vastu:</strong></p>\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<li>The ideal&nbsp;<strong>wardrobe position as per Vastu&nbsp;</strong>is in the south-west direction.</li>\n<li>Another preferred direction as per the&nbsp;<strong>wardrobe Vastu&nbsp;</strong>is the north-west direction.</li>\n<li>Moreover, the south and west walls are the best positions to place a heavy almirah.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Locker Direction as per Vastu</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">For those who are keen to know the&nbsp;<strong>locker direction as per Vastu</strong>, check out the following pointers given below:</p>\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n<li><strong>Vastu for locker in bedroom&nbsp;</strong>should be placed in south direction. However, the locker should be facing or pointing to the north.</li>\n<li>Placing the locker in the south-west or north-east is not recommended.</li>\n<li>The back of the locker should be on the south wall.</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>\n\n        <section class=\"sc_fs_faq sc_card\">\n            <div>\n\t\t\t\t<h2>1.Where a mirror should be placed in Feng Shui?</h2>                <div>\n\t\t\t\t\t                    <p>\n\t\t\t\t\t\tAccording to Feng Shui, mirrors are the key source to reflect both positive and negative energy to your homes. Therefore, mirrors should be placed per the angle and position of your home. Moreover \u2013<br>&#8211; Mirrors can 